Feature: Auto-generated Recipe IDs
  As a game designer
  I want recipe IDs to be auto-generated by the server
  So that I don't have to manually enter unique IDs and risk collisions

  Background:
    Given the world "Ooze Surfers" exists
    And a user is logged in as admin
    And the user is on the Recipes page

  Scenario: Create a recipe without manual ID
    When the user fills in the recipe form fields (name, description, inputs, outputs)
    And the user submits the form
    Then the server should auto-generate a unique ID for the recipe
    And the recipe should appear in the recipe list
    And the recipe ID should be visible in the recipe detail view

  Scenario: Auto-generated IDs are unique
    When the user creates 10 recipes with the same name "Supreme Pizza"
    Then each recipe should have a unique ID
    And no two recipes should share the same ID

  Scenario: Existing recipes retain their IDs
    Given there is an existing recipe with ID "pizza-margherita"
    When the system migration runs
    Then the recipe "pizza-margherita" should still exist with its original ID
    And it should still be usable in crafting

  Scenario: Admin form has no manual ID field
    When the user opens the recipe creation form
    Then there should be no "ID" or "Recipe ID" input field
    And the form should only show: name, description, inputs, outputs

  Scenario: Recipe update preserves auto-generated ID
    Given a recipe exists with auto-generated ID "supreme-pizza"
    When the user edits the recipe name to "Supreme Pizza Deluxe"
    And the user saves the changes
    Then the recipe ID should remain "supreme-pizza"
    And the updated name should be displayed

  Scenario: Recipe ID format is human-readable
    When the user creates a recipe with name "Spicy Pepperoni Feast"
    Then the auto-generated ID should be a readable slug like "spicy-pepperoni-feast"
    And the ID should not contain spaces or special characters
